    <bioghist id="aspace_3c109e4714f8b5b9c8a8c2ccba99195a">
      <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
      <p>Born Reva Fine, in New York, N.Y. 1927. AB English and Philosophy, Hunter College.
        Copywriter at Gimbels department store 1949-1951; Macy's 1951-1953. Junior copywriter at
        Ogilvy &amp; Mather 1953. Career at Ogilvy &amp; Mather: Senior Vice President 1962;
        Associate Copy Chief 1963; first female elected to Board of Directors 1975; U.S. Creative
        Head 1980; retired 1983. Published novel "Having It All" in 1991. Died 2008.</p>
    </bioghist>
