    <scopecontent id="aspace_1d026999fd457eae88eb3d70af321ee3">
      <head>Scope and Contents</head>
      <p>Collection spans 1952-1991 and includes correspondence, storyboards and commercial scripts,
        reports, print advertisements and drafts of Korda's writings including her novel Having It
        All and television pilot proposal scripts. Companies represented include Gillette Gimbel's
        and Macy's department stores, Ogilvy &amp; Mather, Hathaway shirts, Pepperidge Farm and
        Schweppes. Cosmetics advertising includes Gillette (Eve of Roma), Helena Rubenstein and
        Unilever (Dove soap). Acquired as part of the John W. Hartman Center for Sales, Advertising
        &amp; Marketing History.</p>
    </scopecontent>
